                            <comment id="433141" author="hongchao.zhang" created="Tue, 29 Oct 2024 10:18:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/04a76d46-7b8f-42d4-8521-7e393bfde9e7&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/04a76d46-7b8f-42d4-8521-7e393bfde9e7&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
The issue can be reproduced at Maloo, it should be caused by the large data processing of &quot;eval&quot; function in Bash on PPC64le&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;test_get_allquota() {
        ...
        eval $($LFS quota -a -s $start_qid -e $end_qid -u $MOUNT |
            awk &apos;NR &amp;gt; 2 {printf(&quot;u_blimits[%d]=%d;u_ilimits[%d]=%d; \
                 u_busage2[%d]=%d;u_iusage2[%d]=%d;&quot;, \
                 NR, $5, NR, $9, NR, $3, NR, $7)}&apos;)
        ...
}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The test will fail if the quota count is be retrieved by LFS is 5000 (SLOW=yes), there is no failure if the count is 1000 (SLOW=no)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/60e90159-3d13-49bc-9eb8-2653809b0d55&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/60e90159-3d13-49bc-9eb8-2653809b0d55&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
the debug patch passed with setting count = 1000&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
